The paper deals with signal detection and channel estimation in large scale multiuser MIMO systems, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The use of randomized sampling methods and Markov chain Monte Carlo techniques also suggests a possible fit under the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a novel receiver architecture for multiuser MIMO systems, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the proposed receiver architecture in frequency selective fading channels, which could also suggest a possible fit under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
